section*
  code $loinc#67852-4 Hospital Admission evaluation note
  title Admission evaluation
  text """Ms. Laura Mendes, a 45-year-old female, is currently under active oncological treatment for invasive ductal carcinoma of the left breast (ER+/HER2-), Stage IIb. She has completed cycle 2 of 6 of the TC chemotherapy regimen (Docetaxel + Cyclophosphamide).<p/>Recent laboratory results from Provider A show neutropenia (0.9 x10^9/L), mild anaemia (Hb 10.4 g/dL), and a mild ALT elevation, consistent with chemotherapy-related toxicity. Renal function is preserved (creatinine normal). Filgrastim is used on a PRN basis depending on neutrophil count.<p/>A known allergy to iodine contrast media (moderate reaction) is documented and must be flagged for any planned imaging."""
